---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <BaseHead title={`Getting Started — ${SITE_TITLE}`} description="Learn Astro, build your blog, and iterate. A step-by-step guide." />
</head>
<body>
  <Header />
  <main class="container">
    <article class="prose getting-started">
      <h1>Getting Started</h1>
      <p class="lead">From zero Astro knowledge to publishing your first post in 30 minutes. Learn, build, iterate.</p>

      <hr />

      <h2>Prerequisites</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Node.js 22+</strong> — <code>node --version</code></li>
        <li><strong>Git</strong> — for version control and deployment</li>
        <li><strong>VS Code</strong> — recommended (install the <a href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=astro-build.astro-vscode" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Astro extension</a>)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>1. Clone & Run</h2>
      <p>Get the blog running locally in under 5 minutes:</p>
      <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/GauravAgarwalGarg/Blog.git
cd Blog
npm install
npm run dev</code></pre>
      <p>Open <a href="http://localhost:4321/Blog">http://localhost:4321/Blog</a>. You're running.</p>

      <h2>2. Write Your First Post</h2>
      <p>Create <code>src/content/blog/my-first-post.md</code>:</p>
      <pre><code>---
title: "My First Post"
description: "A short description for SEO and social cards."
pubDate: 2024-06-15
category: "software-engineering"
tags: ["learning", "astro"]
draft: false
---

## Hello World

This is my first blog post. It supports full Markdown.</code></pre>

      <h3>Frontmatter Fields</h3>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Field</th><th>Required</th><th>Description</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>title</code></td><td>✅</td><td>Post title</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>description</code></td><td>✅</td><td>SEO description (&lt; 160 chars)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>pubDate</code></td><td>✅</td><td>Publication date (YYYY-MM-DD)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>category</code></td><td>❌</td><td>One of the defined categories</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>tags</code></td><td>❌</td><td>Searchable tags (array)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>draft</code></td><td>❌</td><td><code>true</code> = hidden from listings</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>heroImage</code></td><td>❌</td><td>Hero image (auto-optimized)</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2>3. Add Images</h2>
      <p>Place images in <code>src/assets/</code> and reference them in frontmatter:</p>
      <pre><code>---
heroImage: "../../assets/my-image.jpg"
---</code></pre>
      <p>Astro automatically converts to WebP/AVIF, generates responsive sizes, adds width/height (no CLS), and lazy-loads below the fold.</p>

      <h2>4. Use MDX for Interactive Posts</h2>
      <p>Create <code>.mdx</code> files to embed components inside your Markdown:</p>
      <pre><code>---
title: "Interactive Post"
description: "A post with embedded components."
pubDate: 2024-06-17
category: "emerging-tech"
tags: ["mdx", "interactive"]
---

import MyChart from '../../components/MyChart.astro';

Regular Markdown works here.

&lt;MyChart client:visible /&gt;

The `client:visible` directive means JavaScript only loads
when the component scrolls into view (Islands Architecture).</code></pre>

      <h2>5. Build & Deploy</h2>
      <pre><code># Build for production
npm run build

# Preview the build locally
npm run preview

# Deploy: just push to main
git add .
git commit -m "feat: add new post"
git push origin main</code></pre>
      <p>GitHub Actions automatically builds and deploys to Pages. Zero config.</p>

      <h2>6. Customize</h2>
      <div class="customize-grid">
        <div class="customize-item">
          <h4>Site Info</h4>
          <p>Edit <code>src/consts.ts</code> — title, description, nav links, social links, projects.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="customize-item">
          <h4>Theme Colors</h4>
          <p>Edit <code>src/styles/global.css</code> — light theme in <code>:root</code>, dark in <code>[data-theme="dark"]</code>.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="customize-item">
          <h4>New Pages</h4>
          <p>Create <code>src/pages/my-page.astro</code> — automatically available at <code>/Blog/my-page</code>.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <hr />

      <h2>Learning Astro</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Resource</th><th>Link</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Astro Docs (official)</td><td><a href="https://docs.astro.build/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">docs.astro.build</a></td></tr>
          <tr><td>Astro Tutorial (build a blog)</td><td><a href="https://docs.astro.build/en/tutorial/0-introduction/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Tutorial</a></td></tr>
          <tr><td>Content Collections</td><td><a href="https://docs.astro.build/en/guides/content-collections/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Guide</a></td></tr>
          <tr><td>View Transitions</td><td><a href="https://docs.astro.build/en/guides/view-transitions/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Guide</a></td></tr>
          <tr><td>Islands Architecture</td><td><a href="https://docs.astro.build/en/concepts/islands/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Concept</a></td></tr>
          <tr><td>Image Optimization</td><td><a href="https://docs.astro.build/en/guides/images/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Guide</a></td></tr>
          <tr><td>MDX Integration</td><td><a href="https://docs.astro.build/en/guides/integrations-guide/mdx/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Guide</a></td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <hr />

      <h2>Iteration Cycle</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Write content (Markdown/MDX)</li>
        <li>Preview locally (<code>npm run dev</code>)</li>
        <li>Commit & push (auto-deploys)</li>
        <li>Check Lighthouse score (target: 100/100)</li>
        <li>Repeat</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="rhythm-box">
        <h4>Suggested Weekly Rhythm</h4>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Monday</strong> — Write one long-form post (draft)</li>
          <li><strong>Wednesday</strong> — Edit and publish</li>
          <li><strong>Friday</strong> — 2-3 micro-posts (quick thoughts, links)</li>
          <li><strong>Weekend</strong> — Read, research, collect ideas</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</body>
</html>

<style>
  .getting-started {
    padding: 3rem 0;
  }
  .lead {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
  .customize-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(200px, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }
  .customize-item {
    padding: 1rem;
    background: var(--bg-secondary);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 8px;
  }
  .customize-item h4 {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .customize-item p {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .rhythm-box {
    padding: 1.25rem;
    background: var(--bg-secondary);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }
  .rhythm-box h4 {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .rhythm-box ul {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }
  .rhythm-box li {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }
</style>
